<PageLayout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	subtitle="Effective Date: February 20, 2026"
	description="Privacy policy for futurevotersacademy.org, operated by Future Voters Academy."
>
	<section>
		<h2>Overview</h2>
		<p>
			This privacy policy describes how Future Voters Academy ("FVA," "we," "us") handles
			information in connection with this website, futurevotersacademy.org. FVA is committed to
			protecting the privacy of visitors and the individuals who contact us.
		</p>
		<p>
			This is a static informational website. We do not operate a user account system, online
			donation platform, or subscription service. The scope of information we handle is minimal.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
		<p>This website does not use:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Tracking cookies or advertising cookies</li>
			<li>Third-party analytics platforms such as Google Analytics</li>
			<li>Social media tracking pixels</li>
			<li>Behavioral advertising tools</li>
			<li>User registration or account creation systems</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			We do not collect personal information from visitors passively or automatically.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Information Collected Through Email Contact</h2>
		<p>
			If you contact us by email at fva.info.contact@gmail.com, we will receive your name, email
			address, and the content of your message. This information is used solely to respond to
			your inquiry.
		</p>
		<p>
			We do not share, sell, rent, or distribute contact information to any third party. We do
			not store contact information in any database beyond the email account used to receive it.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Email Communications</h2>
		<p>
			FVA does not send unsolicited promotional emails or newsletters. Contacting us by email
			does not subscribe you to any mailing list. If FVA develops a newsletter or announcement
			mailing list in the future, subscription will require explicit opt-in consent.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Links to External Sites</h2>
		<p>
			This website may link to external government resources, civic organizations, or third-party
			websites. FVA is not responsible for the content or privacy practices of those sites. We
			encourage visitors to review the privacy policies of any external site they visit.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
		<p>
			This website is intended for a general adult audience. FVA does not knowingly collect
			information from children under the age of 13. If you believe a child has submitted
			information to us, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
		<p>
			This privacy policy may be updated as FVA grows and its operations change. The effective
			date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the
			website after a policy update constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Contact</h2>
		<p>
			Questions or concerns about this privacy policy can be directed to Future Voters Academy at{' '}
			<a href="mailto:fva.info.contact@gmail.com">fva.info.contact@gmail.com</a>.
		</p>
	</section>
</PageLayout>
